Alice Police have opened a case of murder after a fatal stabbing of a 30-year-old man in the early hours of Saturday morning. Provincial spokesperson Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana said it was alleged that the deceased was walking with his friends at High street in Alice when he was stabbed with a knife in his upper body by an unidentified person. “He was treated by paramedics and rushed to hospital afterwards, where he succumbed to his wound upon arrival,” he said. Kinana said the suspect is unknown and a case of murder is under investigation and, no arrest has been made yet,” he said. This is a developing story.